{"name": "bsdiff4", "metadata": {"name": "bsdiff4", "version": "1.2.5", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: C", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": "https://github.com/ilanschnell/bsdiff4", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "binary diff and patch using the BSDIFF4-format", "upload_time": 1728533789}, "documentation": ["# bsdiff4: binary diff and patch using the BSDIFF4-format\n\nThe code is mostly derived from cx_bsdiff (written by Anthony Tuininga,\n<http://cx-bsdiff.sourceforge.net/>). The cx_bsdiff code in turn was derived\nfrom bsdiff, the standalone utility produced for BSD which can be found\nat <http://www.daemonology.net/bsdiff>.\nIn addition to the two functions (diff and patch) cx_bsdiff provides, this\npackage includes:\n\n- an interface to the BSDIFF4-format\n- command line interfaces: bsdiff4 and bspatch4\n- tests\n\nThe bsdiff4 package defines the following high level functions:\n\n`diff(src_bytes, dst_bytes)` -> bytes\n\n: Return a BSDIFF4-format patch (from `src_bytes` to `dst_bytes`) as\n  bytes.\n\n`patch(src_bytes, patch_bytes)` -> bytes\n\n: Apply the BSDIFF4-format `patch_bytes` to `src_bytes` and return\n  the bytes.\n\n`file_diff(src_path, dst_path, patch_path)`\n\n: Write a BSDIFF4-format patch (from the file `src_path` to the\n  file `dst_path`) to the file `patch_path`.\n\n`file_patch(src_path, dst_path, patch_path)`\n\n: Apply the BSDIFF4-format file `patch_path` to the file `src_path`\n  and write the result to the file `dst_path`.\n\n`file_patch_inplace(path, patch_path)`\n\n: Apply the BSDIFF4-format file `patch_path` to the file `path`\n  in place.\n\nExample:\n\n```python\n>>> import bsdiff4\n>>> a = 100000 * b'a'\n>>> b = bytearray(a)\n>>> b[100:106] = b' diff '\n>>> p = bsdiff4.diff(a, bytes(b))\n>>> len(p)\n154\n>>> bsdiff4.patch(a, p) == b\nTrue\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.kwds", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.pat", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.data", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "bsdiff4", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "bsdiff4.test", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "verbosity", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "bsdiff4.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "bsdiff4.absolute_import", "xref": {"fqname": "__future__.absolute_import", "project": null}}, {"name": "bsdiff4.diff", "xref": {"fqname": "bsdiff4.format.diff", "project": null}}, {"name": "bsdiff4.file_diff", "xref": {"fqname": "bsdiff4.format.file_diff", "project": null}}, {"name": "bsdiff4.file_patch", "xref": {"fqname": "bsdiff4.format.file_patch", "project": null}}, {"name": "bsdiff4.file_patch_inplace", "xref": {"fqname": "bsdiff4.format.file_patch_inplace", "project": null}}, {"name": "bsdiff4.patch", "xref": {"fqname": "bsdiff4.format.patch", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "bsdiff4.format", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "bsdiff4.format.write_patch", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fo", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "len_dst", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tcontrol", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bdiff", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bextra", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["write a BSDIFF4-format patch to stream 'fo'\n    "]}, {"name": "bsdiff4.format.read_patch", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fi", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "header_only", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["read a BSDIFF4-format patch from stream 'fi'\n    "]}, {"name": "bsdiff4.format.read_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bsdiff4.format.diff", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src_bytes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dst_bytes", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["diff(src_bytes, dst_bytes) -> bytes\n\nReturn a BSDIFF4-format patch (from src_bytes to dst_bytes) as bytes."]}, {"name": "bsdiff4.format.file_diff", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dst_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "patch_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["file_diff(src_path, dst_path, patch_path)\n\nWrite a BSDIFF4-format patch (from the file src_path to the file dst_path)\nto the file patch_path."]}, {"name": "bsdiff4.format.patch", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src_bytes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "patch_bytes", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["patch(src_bytes, patch_bytes) -> bytes\n\nApply the BSDIFF4-format patch_bytes to src_bytes and return the bytes."]}, {"name": "bsdiff4.format.file_patch_inplace", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "patch_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["file_patch_inplace(path, patch_path)\n\nApply the BSDIFF4-format file patch_path to the file 'path' in place."]}, {"nam